Base:Descriptions.Base:Description: A {lean|feral} looking dog-fox about a foot tall with a pointed muzzle, triangular ears, tilted brown eyes, a furry body and four lithe legs. He has a long bushy tail with a white {brush|tip}.
A lean dog fox with rust-coloured fur and a long bushy tail.
The fox's chest is covered in a patch of lush white fur that runs beneath his belly.
The fox's ear is {triangular|pointed} with a black tip.
The fox's pair of ears is {triangular|pointed} with black tips.
The cunning brown eye of a fox.
The brown eye of a fox.
A pair of cunning brown fox eyes. They are slitted and return your gaze warily.
A pair of brown fox eyes.
The fox's coat is a dark, rusty orange-red; the fur long and wiry with white on the chest running along the belly. The tip of the tail is also white.
The fox's coat is a dark rusty orange-red, with white on the chest running along the belly. The tip of the tail is also white.
The fox's head is covered in rust coloured fur which darkens towards the muzzle.
By observing the chest carefully you detect a heart beating.

The lithe, rust-coloured legs of a fox.
The fur on the dog-fox's pointed muzzle is darker than that of the head and ends in a wet black nose.
The neck of a fox is lined with shaggy rusty-red fur.
